# Instruction for installing fluidd on K1/K1Max 3D printers

## prerequisite 
enable root access for your K1/K1Max printer in the settings menu of your touch screen display

## get and install fluidd

ssh as root:

```
$ ssh root@192.168.1.x
root@192.168.1.x's password:  # default password is creality_2023 
root@K1Max-1 /root [#] cd /usr/data/
root@K1Max-1 /usr/data [#] wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CrealityOfficial/K1_Series_Annex/main/fluidd/fluidd/fluidd.sh
root@K1Max-1 /usr/data [#] wget https://raw.githubusercontent.com/CrealityOfficial/K1_Series_Annex/main/fluidd/fluidd/fluidd.tar
root@K1Max-1 /usr/data [#] chmod 744 fluidd.sh
```

Install fluidd, moonraker and nginx
```
root@K1Max-1 /usr/data [#] ./fluidd install
```

unstall fluidd, moonraker and nginx
```
root@K1Max-1 /usr/data [#] ./fluidd uninstall
```

## access fluidd

Fluidd opens a port on 4408, so you can access it for example via:
http://192.168.1.x:4408

## remarks

Warning: Monnraker running for a long time on the K1 series poses a risk of memory overflow
